121. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock
Problem

You are given:

prices[i]

where prices[i] is the stock price on day i.

You must:

Buy first
then sell later

Find the maximum profit possible.

If no profit is possible, return:

0
Brute Force Approach
Intuition

Try every possible pair:

Buy on day i
Sell on day j

where:

j > i

Calculate all profits and take maximum.

Brute Force Code
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {

        int maxProfit = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < prices.length; i++) {

            for(int j = i + 1; j < prices.length; j++) {

                int profit = prices[j] - prices[i];

                maxProfit = Math.max(maxProfit, profit);
            }
        }

        return maxProfit;
    }
}
Complexity
Time Complexity
O(n²)
Space Complexity
O(1)
Optimal Approach
Main Intuition

To maximize profit:

Buy at minimum price
Sell at maximum price after it

So while traversing:

Keep track of minimum price seen so far
Calculate profit if sold today
Update maximum profit
Core Idea

Maintain:

minPrice  → lowest buying price till now
maxProfit → best profit till now
Algorithm
Step 1

Store minimum price seen so far.

minPrice = Math.min(minPrice, prices[i])
Step 2

Profit if sold today:

profit = prices[i] - minPrice
Step 3

Update maximum profit.

maxProfit = Math.max(maxProfit, profit)
